<DOC><DOCNO> AP881111-0266 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-11-88 1319EST</FILEID><FIRST>u f BC-TheWeekAhead     11-11 0393</FIRST><SECOND>BC-The Week Ahead,0423</SECOND><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Here are the major business events and economic events scheduledfor the coming week (some dates are tentative):</TEXT><BYLINE>MONDAY, Nov. 14</BYLINE><TEXT>      ATLANTA _ A federal judge may rule today on West Point-PepperellInc.'s attempt to block a $1.4 billion takeover bid by Farley Inc.and on Farley's lawsuit seeking to have Georgia's new anti-takeoverlaw declared unconstitutional.   NEW YORK _ The American Petroleum Institute's annual meeting runsthrough Tuesday.   WILMINGTON, Del. _ The head of Polaroid Corp. is scheduled to becross-examined in a Chancery Court trial of Shamrock Holdings' suitseeking to overturn Polaroid's restructuring.   WASHINGTON _ The Supreme Court plans to announce orders andpossibly decisions.</TEXT><BYLINE>TUESDAY, Nov. 15</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ The Commerce Department is to release a report onoverall retail sales during October; due at 8:30 a.m. EST.   WASHINGTON _ The Federal Reserve is reporting on industrialproduction during October; due at 9:15 a.m. EST.   DETROIT _ Domestic automakers are scheduled to report their salesof cars and light trucks during the first 10 days of November.</TEXT><BYLINE>WEDNESDAY, Nov. 16</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ The Commerce Department is reporting on the nation'sforeign trade balance for September; due at 8:30 a.m. EST.   WASHINGTON _ The Commerce Department also plans to report onbusiness inventories and sales during September; due at 10 a.m. EST.   WASHINGTON _ The Federal Reserve is to report on factory capacityin use during October; release time uncertain.   WASHINGTON _ The National Economic Commission has scheduled apublic hearing on the budget deficit.</TEXT><BYLINE>THURSDAY, Nov. 17</BYLINE><TEXT>      VIENNA, Austria _ OPEC's pricing and strategy committees plan tomeet before the oil cartel's full ministerial session scheduled tobegin Nov. 21.   WASHINGTON _ The Commerce Department is reporting on the numberof new housing units started during October; due at 8:30 a.m. EST.   PITTSBURGH _ A bankruptcy court judge set today as the deadlinefor the board of Allegheny International Inc. to choose between tworival takeover</TEXT><BYLINE>FRIDAY, Nov. 18</BYLINE><TEXT>      ATLANTA _ RJR Nabisco Corp.'s special committee of outsidedirectors set today as the deadline for the submission of takeoverbids for the consumer product and tobacco giant.   BRUSSELS, Belgium _ U.S. Trade Representative Clayton Yeutter andAgriculture Secretary Richard Lyng plan to hold trade talks atEuropean Economic Community headquarters.</TEXT></DOC>